            "answer_text": "First things first. A ball pen which is light in color when bought, writes dark later due to the smoothness of the nib that was created out of writing for longer periods. So what we need for a pen to write dark is the nib of an old pen which writes dark and whose ink ran out. The next step is simple. Replace new pen nib with old pen nib. Voila! :D If u don't have a dark writing pen, go to any shop and exchange a new pen for the pen with the guy sitting behind counter. ;D It always writes dark. Sometimes if the new pen with old nib stops writing after few lines, it means that the old ink in the nib is finished and the new ink didn't reach the ball yet. So jerk the pen in downward motion few times, to force the ink to drop on to the ball. It will work again ! ",
