            "answer_text": "A ballpoint pen will typically not write dark for one of two reasons: The ink just isn't dark by natureThis usually isn't the case, as ballpoints typically have pretty dark ink.Perhaps you can find a replacement cartridge that's darker.The ink is not flowing well (the pen has \u201cdried up\u201d)In this case, if there is still ink left in the pen, you may be able to get it flowing again.To do so, take the ballpoint cartridge out, and hold the metal tip over the edge for a few seconds, rotating it as you do.The heat from the flame should be enough to reconstitute the ink and get your ballpoint going again!I hope this helps! :) ",
